Hungary Wooing Sovereign Funds, Eyeing Islamic, Ruble Bond Sale

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-09-30T10:09:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/hungary-wooing-sovereign-funds-eyeing-islamic-ruble-bond-sale.html
Hungary  is trying to woo sovereign
funds including that of  Norway  and  Saudi Arabia  to be long-term
investors in the Hungarian forint debt market, Debt Management
Agency Chief Executive Officer Gyula Pleschinger said.  The country is also considering selling Islamic and Russian
ruble bonds, Pleschinger told a conference in Pecs, southern
Hungary today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Zoltan Simon at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net  